<subSubSection id="92A826F8E810FFDCFF42FB7E2FEFFAAF" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="DA0D7573E810FFDCFF42FB7E2FEFFAAF" blockId="17.[192,1440,1247,1401]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
Regarding only extant taxa, 
<taxonomicName id="1DB20EF0E810FFDCFD95FB7E28FAFB21" authorityName="Perez-Gelabert and Yong" authorityYear="2014" box="[575,693,1247,1270]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Armasius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E8C6A961E810FFDCFD95FB7E28FAFB21" box="[575,693,1247,1270]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Armasius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most recent record of cladonotines from the Neotropical region. It was found in 
<collectingCountry id="A2A535E3E810FFDCFE70FAA12854FACF" box="[474,539,1280,1304]" name="Cuba" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Cuba</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BE230882E810FFDCFD83FAA129EDFACF" author="Perez-Gelabert, D. E. &amp; S. Yong" box="[553,930,1280,1304]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" pagination="44 - 50" refId="ref14732" refString="Perez-Gelabert, D. E., and S. Yong. 2014. Armasius iberianus (Orthoptera: Tetrigidae: Cladonotinae): A new genus and species of pygmy grasshoppers from Eastern Cuba. Novitates Caribaea 7: 44 - 50." type="journal article" year="2014">Perez-Gelabert and Yong 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="BE230882E810FFDCFC07FAA12ED2FACF" author="Cigliano, M. M. &amp; H. Braun &amp; D. C. Eades &amp; D. Otte" box="[941,1181,1280,1304]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" refId="ref13879" refString="Cigliano, M. M., H. Braun, D. C. Eades, and D. Otte. 2018. Orthoptera Species File. Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available at http: // Orthoptera. SpeciesFile. org (Last accessed 2 December 2018.)" type="url" year="2018">Cigliano et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="1DB20EF0E810FFDCFB1AFAA1280FFAEF" authority="Perez-Gelabert and Yong, 2014" authorityName="Perez-Gelabert and Yong" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Armasius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iberianus">
<emphasis id="E8C6A961E810FFDCFB1AFAA12FEFFAC0" box="[1200,1440,1279,1303]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Armasius iberianus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BE230882E810FFDCFF6AFA81280FFAEF" author="Perez-Gelabert, D. E. &amp; S. Yong" box="[192,576,1312,1336]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" pagination="44 - 50" refId="ref14732" refString="Perez-Gelabert, D. E., and S. Yong. 2014. Armasius iberianus (Orthoptera: Tetrigidae: Cladonotinae): A new genus and species of pygmy grasshoppers from Eastern Cuba. Novitates Caribaea 7: 44 - 50." type="journal article" year="2014">Perez-Gelabert and Yong, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is the unique species in the genus, which presents the unique characteristic among Neotropical 
<taxonomicName id="1DB20EF0E810FFDCFDA2FAE128E4FA8F" authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[520,683,1344,1368]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cladonotinae">Cladonotinae</taxonomicName>
of a lateral lobe of the pronotum modified as a sharp projection with triangular shape (male) (
<bibRefCitation id="BE230882E810FFDCFD85FAC128FDFAAF" author="Yong, S." box="[559,690,1376,1400]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref15394" refString="Yong, S. 2017. The adult male of the little-known pygmy grasshopper Armasius iberianus Perez-Gelabert and Yong, 2014 (Orthoptera: Tetrigidae: Cladonotinae). Ecologica Montenegrina 15: 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="2017">Yong 2017</bibRefCitation>
) or forming a spine (female) (
<bibRefCitation id="BE230882E810FFDCFBB3FAC12FDBFAAF" author="Perez-Gelabert, D. E. &amp; S. Yong" box="[1049,1428,1376,1401]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" pagination="44 - 50" refId="ref14732" refString="Perez-Gelabert, D. E., and S. Yong. 2014. Armasius iberianus (Orthoptera: Tetrigidae: Cladonotinae): A new genus and species of pygmy grasshoppers from Eastern Cuba. Novitates Caribaea 7: 44 - 50." type="journal article" year="2014">Perez-Gelabert and Yong 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
